article.headline: Valparaiso 66, Centenary 62
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Jake Diebler scored 16 points as Valparaiso edged by Centenary 66-62 in their Mid-Continent Conference opener on Thursday. Centenary (6-10, 0-1) raced out to an early 12-3 lead on six points by Nick Stallings and four from Tyrone Hamilton while holding Valparaiso to just three points for the first 6:37 of the contest. The Crusaders (6-8, 1-0) quickly pulled to within two, 14-12, and then grabbed their first lead of the game at 20-18 with 3:41 left in the opening half. Still on top at 22-20, Diebler hit the first of his four 3-pointers with 22 seconds left to raise their advantage to 25-20 at the break. Urule Igbavboa added 14 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for Valparaiso. Brandon McPherson finished with 12 points and Samuel Haanpaa added 10. Larry Logan scored 16 points and had 15 rebounds to lead Centenary, while Alexander Starr added 15 points, Hamilton had 12 and Stallings 11.
